release checklist:
1. Check the output of the test suite
2. Check the output of 'git status' above - is everything in the repository?
3. Version numbers
3a. Have you set the VERSION string in the Makefile to the new version?
3b. Check above if the version number and date are set correctly in the Changes file
4. Check the contents of the source code package
5. Check the contents of the binary package
6. Create the release announcement
7. Add the new version to the website
8. Commit the website changes
9. Create a git tag
10. Copy announcement and the packages to the website: 'make copy-website copy-packages-website'
